0RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk0MjQyMTYx"},"nonce":"BfOzwpQYCcGQYR1FnzImzWZsyXA=","target":"f09943f518304ce36392f56cecde43949b52ebfd1b639cd22ba7542ca7587ab4","message":"I wouldn't want to get into a discussion about terminology, but TRNG can't be constructed (solely) algorithmically apriori.\n\nIn addition, to talk about large periods, you should prove that there are no cycles in your generator, at least for some subset of initial seeds. For instance, take look at [wyrand](https://github.com/wangyi-fudan/wyhash/blob/d15d6e7ebee5f408e362ba171708b00a4bb52574/wyhash.h#L118): it has an obvious period of 2^64 and a fairly understandable statistical skew due to the non-injectivity of the MUM transformation.\n\n@wangyi-fudan, @lemire, FYI.","files":null}]}